The
 owners of a 22-pound housecat that trapped them in their bedroom after 
attacking their baby insist they are not giving up on their pet and are 
instead getting it therapy.

Two
 days after police arrived to subdue the four-year-old part-Himalayan 
cat, owner Lee Palmer of Portland said he is taking the feline to a 
veterinarian.

A pet psychologist also is due at the house to see the cat, named Lux.

