'We're not getting rid of him right now,' Palmer said. 'He's been part of our family for a long time.'

Palmer says the animal attacked his seven-month-old child after the baby pulled its tail.

The child suffered a few scratches on the forehead.

On the 911 call, Palmer tells the dispatcher he kicked the cat 'in the rear' to protect his child.

